sub_topic: Identifying the automorphism group of a graph.
message_1: Consider a graph with 7 vertices and 9 edges. What is the automorphism group of this graph?
message_2:
To determine the automorphism group of a graph with 7 vertices and 9 edges, we need more information about the structure of the graph. The automorphism group of a graph is the set of all graph automorphisms (permutations of the vertices that preserve the edge structure). Different graphs with 7 vertices and 9 edges can have different automorphism groups.

For example, if the graph is a cycle of length 7 with two additional edges connecting two non-adjacent vertices, its automorphism group will be different from a graph formed by joining two cycles of length 4 and 3 with a single edge.

Please provide more information about the structure of the graph or a specific example, and then we can determine the automorphism group.
